{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place water in mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket and add sweet potatoes to it then steam <nobr>20-25 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove simmering basket using spatula and transfer sweet potatoes to a bowl. Allow to cool at room temperature for 40 minutes. Clean mixing bowl.","Place lime juice, garlic cloves, coriander leaves, 40 g red onion, habanero chilli, clam juice and ice cubes in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Strain tiger milk through a sieve into a medium bowl.","Add to the liquid 40 g red onion, sea bass, salmon and salt and allow to marinate for 2-3 minutes. Meanwhile, halve sweet potatoes lengthwise and using a small melon baller, scoop out potato balls and add to ceviche.","Using a slotted spoon, divide ceviche between 6 small bowls or onto 6 plates. Drizzle ceviche with tiger milk, garnish with coriander leaves and serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["500 g water","2 sweet potatoes, unpeeled (approx. 150 g each)","150 g lime juice, freshly squeezed","2 garlic cloves","2 Tbsp coriander leaves, plus extra to garnish","80 g red onion, 40 g thinly sliced","½ habanero chilli, seeded","50 g clam juice              (optional)","4 ice cubes","300 g fresh sea bass fillets, skinless, cubed (1 cm)","300 g fresh salmon fillets, skinless, cubed (1 cm)","½ tsp fine sea salt"]}],"id":"r208379","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-SQyT3WOy06Y\/XZMvZD22M2I\/AAAAAAAAaRQ\/BCQV7--RyvozCA7hfQYBfMpU69Co3TMbQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_eqTFVRWkqm5bos2M.png","title":"Peruvian Ceviche","publishedAt":"2017-09-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"20 g","fat":"10 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"13 g","calories":"947 kJ \/ 226 kcal"},"usefulItems":"slotted spoon, melon baller, fine mesh sieve","hintsAndTricks":["Leche de tigre, or tiger's milk, is the Peruvian term for a citrus-based marinade that cures the seafood in a ceviche. Also known as leche de pantera, this leftover fish runoff usually contains lime juice, sliced onion, chillies, salt and pepper - along with some fish juice. <br>In Peru, this invigorating potion is often served alongside ceviche in a small glass and believed to be both a hangover cure as well as an aphrodisiac!"],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 15m","6 portions"]}